claimableDepositRequest(uint256,address).details: This function always reverts because this implementation does not have async deposits.

params: 1 The address of the controller (Not used in this implementation)

returns._0: This function never returns; it always reverts

claimableRedeemRequest(uint256,address).details: A redeem request is considered claimable if it has reached or passed the claimable delay period

params: 0 The ID of the redeem request (unused, as we have 1 request per user at a time)
params.controller: The address of the request's controller

returns._0: uint256 The amount of shares in the claimable redeem request, or 0 if no claimable request exists

constructor.details: Sets up the vault's configuration, strategy, and initial roles

params.params: A struct containing all necessary initialization parameters, see ConstructorParams for details

deposit(uint256,address).details: This function overrides the ERC4626 deposit functionIt can only be called when the vault is not halted

params.assets: The amount of assets to deposit
params.receiver: The address that will receive the minted shares

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

isOperator(address,address).details: This function verifies if the given operator address has been authorized for the specified account

params.account: The address of the account to check
params.operator: The address of the potential operator for the account.

returns._0: bool Returns true if the operator is authorized for the account, false otherwise

maxDeposit(address).details: This function overrides the maxDeposit function from ERC4626Returns the smaller of the maxDepositPerTransaction and the remaining vault capacity

params: 0 The address that would receive the minted shares (unused in this implementation)

returns._0: The maximum amount of assets that can be deposited

maxMint(address).details: This function overrides the maxMint function from ERC4626Calculates the maximum shares by converting the maximum deposit amount to shares

params.receiver: The address that would receive the minted shares (unused in this implementation)

returns._0: The maximum amount of shares that can be minted

maxRedeem(address).details: This function overrides the ERC4626 maxRedeem functionWe don't have partial redeems, so the return value is either 0 or all the shares in a request.

params.controller: The address of the controller attempting to redeem

returns._0: uint256 The maximum number of shares that can be redeemed, or 0 if redemption is not possible

maxWithdraw(address).details: Returns the maximum amount of assets that can be withdrawn from the vault for a given owner.

params: 0 The address of the account to check the maximum withdrawal for (unused in this implementation)

returns._0: Always returns 0 because withdraws are not supported in this vault, only redeems are available.

mint(uint256,address).details: This function overrides the ERC4626 mint functionIt can only be called when the vault is not halted

params.receiver: The address that will receive the minted shares
params.shares: The amount of shares to mint

pendingDepositRequest(uint256,address).details: This function always reverts because this implementation does not have async deposits.

params: 1 The address of the controller (Not used in this implementation)

returns._0: This function never returns; it always reverts

pendingRedeemRequest(uint256,address).details: A redeem request is considered pending if it hasn't reached the claimable delay period

params: 0 The ID of the redeem request (unused, as we have 1 request per user at a time)
params.controller: The address of the request's controller

returns._0: uint256 The amount of shares in the pending redeem request, or 0 if no pending request exists

previewRedeem(uint256).details: This function always reverts because it's not possible to preview a redeem because they are async.

params: 0 The amount of shares that would be redeemed (Not used in this implementation)

returns._0: This function never returns; it always reverts

previewWithdraw(uint256).details: This function always reverts because the withdraw function is not available in this vault. Only redeem functionality is supported.

params: 0 The amount of assets that would be withdrawn

returns._0: This function never returns; it always reverts

rebalanceAssets(address).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLEIt ensures that the vault has enough assets to cover all pending redemption requestsIf the vault has more assets than needed, it transfers the excess to the strategyIf the vault has less assets than needed, it transfers the necessary amount from provided address.

params.sourceOfAssets: The address from which to transfer additional assets if needed

redeem(uint256,address,address).details: This function can only be called when the contract is not haltedCaller must be the controller of the redemption request or an approved operatorIt processes the redemption request, burns the claimable shares, and transfers assets to the receiverA redemption fee is applied to the redeemed assets.The actual amount of assets transferred to the receiver will be less than the original requested amount due to this withdrawal fee.

params.controller: The address that controls this redemption request (must be the original caller of the redeem request)
params.receiver: The address that will receive the redeemed assets
params.shares: The number of shares to redeem (must match the original request)

returns._0: The amount of assets transferred to the receiver

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

reportLosses(uint256,string).details: This function can only be called by an account with the PNL_REPORTER_ROLEDecreases the vaultAssets by the reported loss amount

params.assetLossAmount: The amount of loss in asset tokens
params.infoURI: A URI containing additional information about the loss report

returns._0: The total amount of losses reported so far

reportProfits(uint256,string).details: This function can only be called by an account with the PNL_REPORTER_ROLEEven though tokens aren't transferred to the vault, vaultAssets are increased.

params.assetProfitAmount: The amount of profit in asset tokens
params.infoURI: A URI containing additional information about the profit report

returns._0: The total amount of profits reported so far

requestDeposit(uint256).details: This function always reverts because this implementation does not have async deposits.

params: 0 The amount of shares that would be deposited (Not used in this implementation)

returns._0: This function never returns; it always reverts

requestRedeem(uint256,address,address).details: This function can only be called when the contract is not haltedCaller can be any owner of shares, or an approved operator of the owner.It creates a new redemption request or reverts if there's an existing requestNote that the exchange rate between shares and assets is fixed in the request.

params.controller: The address that will control this redemption request (must be caller)
params.owner: The address that owns the shares to be redeemed
params.shares: The number of shares to redeem

returns._0: A uint8 representing the request ID (always 0 in this implementation)

requestRedeem(uint256,address,address,ui.details: This function can only be called when the contract is not haltedCaller can be any owner of shares, or an approved operator of the ownerIt creates a new redemption request or reverts if there's an existing requestThe exchange rate between shares and assets is fixed in the requestReverts if the converted assets are less than the specified minimum

params.controller: The address that will control this redemption request (must be caller)
params.minAssetsOut: The minimum amount of assets expected from the redemption
params.owner: The address that owns the shares to be redeemed
params.shares: The number of shares to redeem

returns._0: A uint8 representing the request ID (always 0 in this implementation)

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setClaimableDelay(uint32).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._newClaimableDelay: The new delay (in seconds) before a redeem request becomes claimable.

setHaltStatus(bool).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._newHaltStatus: The new halt status to set (true for halted, false for not halted)

setMaxDepositPerTransaction(uint128).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._newMaxDepositPerTransaction: The new maximum deposit amount per transaction

setMaxVaultCapacity(uint256).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLEThe new max vault capacity must be higher than the current vaultAssets

params._newMaxVaultCapacity: The new maximum capacity of assets for the vault

setMinDepositPerTransaction(uint128).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._newMinDepositPerTransaction: The new minimum deposit amount per transaction

setOperator(address,bool).details: This function allows users to designate or revoke operator privileges for their account

params._approved: True to approve the operator, false to revoke approval
params._operator: The address to set as an operator or remove operator status from

setRedeemFee(uint16).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._newRedeemFeeBasisPoints: The new redeem fee in basis points (100 basis points = 1%)

setRedeemFeeCollector(address).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._newRedeemFeeCollector: The new address to set as the redeem fee collector

setStrategyName(string).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._newStrategyName: The new name to set for the investment strategy

setStrategyURI(string).details: This function can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._newStrategyURI: The new URI to set for the investment strategy

totalAssets().details: This function overrides the totalAssets function from ERC4626Goes up on deposits/mints and profit reports, goes down on redeems and loss reports.

withdraw(uint256,address,address).details: This function always reverts because withdraws are not supported in this vault, only redeems are available.

params: 2 owner The owner of the assets to withdraw (unused)

returns._0: This function never returns; it always reverts

PNL_REPORTER_ROLE().notice: Role that allows reporting of profits and losses

claimableDelay().notice: The minimum delay between creating a redemption request and when it can be processed

claimableRedeemRequest(uint256,address).notice: Returns the amount of shares in a claimable redeem request for a given controller

constructor.notice: Initializes the vault with the provided parameters

deposit(uint256,address).notice: Deposits assets into the vault and mints shares to the receiver, by specifying the amount of assets.

halted().notice: Indicates whether the vault operations are halted

isOperator(address,address).notice: Checks if an address is an operator for an account

maxDeposit(address).notice: Returns the maximum amount of assets that can be deposited in a single transaction

maxDepositPerTransaction().notice: The maximum amount of assets that can be deposited by a user per deposit transaction

maxMint(address).notice: Returns the maximum amount of shares that can be minted in a single transaction

maxRedeem(address).notice: Returns the maximum amount of shares that can be redeemed by a controller

maxVaultCapacity().notice: The maximum amount of assets that the vault can hold

minDepositPerTransaction().notice: The minimum amount of assets that need to be deposited by a user per deposit transaction

mint(uint256,address).notice: Deposits assets into the vault and mints shares to the receiver, by specifying the amount of shares.

pendingRedeemRequest(uint256,address).notice: Returns the amount of shares in a pending redeem request for a given controller

rebalanceAssets(address).notice: Rebalances assets so that the vault has enough assets, but not more, to cover all pending redemption requests

redeem(uint256,address,address).notice: Redeems shares for assets, completing a previously initiated redemption request

redeemFeeBasisPoints().notice: The fee charged on redeems, expressed in basis points

redeemFeeCollector().notice: The address where redeem fees are sent

redeemRequests(address).notice: Mapping of user addresses to their redeem requests

requestRedeem(uint256,address,address,ui.notice: Requests a redemption of shares with a minimum assets out check

setClaimableDelay(uint32).notice: Sets a new claimable delay for the vault

setHaltStatus(bool).notice: Sets the halt status of the vault

setMaxDepositPerTransaction(uint128).notice: Sets the maximum deposit amount allowed per transaction

setMaxVaultCapacity(uint256).notice: Sets the maximum capacity of assets that the vault can hold

setMinDepositPerTransaction(uint128).notice: Sets the minimum deposit amount allowed per transaction

setOperator(address,bool).notice: Sets or removes an operator for the caller's account

setRedeemFee(uint16).notice: Sets the redeem fee for the vault

setRedeemFeeCollector(address).notice: Sets a new address for the redeem fee collector

setStrategyName(string).notice: Sets a new name for the investment strategy

setStrategyURI(string).notice: Sets a new URI for the investment strategy

totalAssets().notice: Returns the total amount of assets "in" the vault - both assets in the vault for the purpose of withdraws + assets in the strategy.

totalAssetsInRedemptionProcess().notice: Total value of assets currently in the redemption process

totalLossesReported().notice: Total sum of all historical losses reported by the PNL_REPORTER_ROLE admin.

totalProfitsReported().notice: Total sum of all historical profits reported by the PNL_REPORTER_ROLE admin.

totalSharesInRedemptionProcess().notice: Total number of shares currently in the redemption process

vaultAssets().notice: The abstract representation of the total assets in the vault
